<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Microscopic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Spores ellipsoid, sometimes ovoid, pale yellow to yellow brown, guttulate, sometimes weakly, on ave. 10.0-12.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.0-6.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, ave. Q = 1.5-1.8, almost smooth or weakly ornamented (O1O2), perispore not loosening (P0), indextrinoid (D0). Basidia 28-33(-37) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, ave. Q = 3.1-4.4, mostly four-spored. Cheilocystidia lageniform or ventricose, occasionally with characteristic basal or median wall thickening, septate, on ave. 38-45 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6 (apex) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-6 (middle) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-10.5 (base) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, ratios A/M = 1.02-1.10, A/B = 0.51-0.73, B/M = 1.52-2.10. Epicutis an ixocutis, 90-100 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick (measured from exsiccata), maximum hyphae width 6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, sometimes encrusted, trama elements beneath subcutis isodiametric up to 15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide. Caulocystidia similar to cheilocystidia but less ventricose, up to 120 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
